# Codex Writer Findings — publicmenu
Chain: publicmenu-260408-072228-de40

## Findings
1. [P1] New SOS request types are still filtered out of help-sync state — `HELP_REQUEST_TYPES` still allows only `call_waiter`, `bill`, `napkins`, `menu`, and `other` at `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:1796`, and the same old subset is used by ServiceRequest filtering/normalization at `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:2053-2061` and `nonOtherTypes` at `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:2130`. `plate`, `utensils`, and `clear_table` requests will be ignored on fetch/restore, while legacy `menu` still behaves like an active preset. FIX: expand `HELP_REQUEST_TYPES` and `nonOtherTypes` to include the three new types, keep `menu` legacy-only, and align the request whitelist with the v6.0 button set.
2. [P2] Help drawer config constants are still on the legacy card model — `HELP_COOLDOWN_SECONDS` and `HELP_CARD_LABELS` at `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:1799-1806` still cover only waiter/bill/napkins/menu/other, still use `help.bill` and `help.menu`, and there is no `HELP_CARD_SHORT_LABELS`. `HELP_CHIPS` and `HELP_PREVIEW_LIMIT` also remain defined at `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:1795-1813` and are still referenced at `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:2701`, `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:4935`, `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:5027`, and `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:5102`, so the deprecated v5 constants were not removed. FIX: replace the label/cooldown maps with the v6.0 six-button config, add `HELP_CARD_SHORT_LABELS`, and remove the deprecated chip/preview constants once the remaining call sites are handled.
3. [P2] Urgency threshold plumbing is missing — there are no `HELP_URGENCY_THRESHOLDS`, `HELP_URGENCY_GROUP`, `getHelpUrgency`, or `getHelpTimerStr` definitions anywhere in `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx` (file-wide search returned no matches). The safe constants/helper layer for amber/red aging and minute timer strings is absent, so the v6.0 drawer still has no urgency model to consume in the next step. FIX: add the two `useMemo` threshold/group maps immediately after `HELP_COOLDOWN_SECONDS` and add both `useCallback` helpers before the component return.
4. [P1] The fallback dictionaries are incomplete and still mix old help keys/copy — the EN block at `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:525-584` still lacks the new v6.0 keys such as `help.plate`, `help.utensils`, `help.clear_table`, all six `*_short` keys, `help.subtitle_choose`, `help.table_default`, `help.cancel_confirm_q`, `help.cancel_keep`, `help.cancel_do`, `help.other_request_link`, `help.other_placeholder`, and `help.send_btn`. The RU block at `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:588-636` lacks the same additions plus `help.sent_suffix` and `help.undo`, and its existing `help.get_bill` entry at `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:596` still uses the older verbose copy `"Принести счёт"` instead of the required short `"Счёт"`. Once Fix 1 switches labels to the new keys, RU/EN will fall back to raw keys or wrong copy. FIX: add the missing `help.*` entries to both fallback maps and replace RU `help.get_bill` with the shorter v6.0 label.

